I was much pleased with the ingenuity of a Negro, who, when he slept on a journey, always had athis side some resinous material from rotten wood, which glistens at night, smokes gently without any unpleasant 5111611, and, as I observed, always defended him froin gnatS. Incredible is the annoyance caused by these insects in a long journey. We have often re- turned home mangled, swollen, and bloody, in short, so unlike ourselves, that we could hardly know one another.
